    "reasoning": "We first determine N_3, the number of seating arrangements with six alternating blocks of exactly two persons of the same gender each. Considering the seats as labeled (distinct), there are 4 possible gender patterns (rotations of the pattern M,M,W,W,M,M,W,W,M,M,W,W). For each pattern, the adjacency conditions force that each boundary between a men block and a women block must be a married couple. Thus, we assign the 6 couples to the 6 boundary pairs, which can be done in 6! = 720 ways per pattern. So total N_3 = 4 * 720 = 2880. Then k = N_3 - 2879 = 1. The sum S = k/(3^2+1) + k/(4^2+2) + k/(5^2+3) + ... = sum_{n=3}^∞ 1/(n^2+n-2). Using partial fractions, 1/((n+2)(n-1)) = (1/3)(1/(n-1)-1/(n+2)). The series telescopes to (1/3)*(1/2+1/3+1/4) = (1/3)*(13/12) = 13/36.",
